IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. MainBlocksMaximumStateId_TC-1.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT RESULT-FILE ASSIGN TO WS-RESULT-FILE-PATH
        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD RESULT-FILE.
01 RESULT-REC PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
    COPY DD-BLOCKS.
    01 LK-MAXIMUM-ID            BINARY-LONG UNSIGNED.
    01 LK-MAXIMUM-ID-DISPLAY    PIC 9(10).
    01 OUTPUT-LINE              PIC X(80) VALUE SPACES.
    01 WS-RESULT-FILE-PATH      PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
    DISPLAY "MainBlocksMaximumStateId_TC-1 started".
    
    *> Accept result file path from environment
    ACCEPT WS-RESULT-FILE-PATH FROM ENVIRONMENT "RESULT_FILE_PATH"
    
    *> Initialize BLOCKS structure with test value
    MOVE 1000 TO BLOCKS-MAXIMUM-STATE-ID
    
    *> Call the subprogram
    CALL 'Blocks-MaximumStateId' USING LK-MAXIMUM-ID
    DISPLAY "Blocks-MaximumStateId returned LK-MAXIMUM-ID=" LK-MAXIMUM-ID
    
    *> Write outputs to file
    OPEN OUTPUT RESULT-FILE
    MOVE LK-MAXIMUM-ID TO LK-MAXIMUM-ID-DISPLAY
    STRING "LK-MAXIMUM-ID=" DELIMITED BY SIZE
           LK-MAXIMUM-ID-DISPLAY DELIMITED BY SIZE
           INTO OUTPUT-LINE
    END-STRING
    MOVE OUTPUT-LINE TO RESULT-REC
    WRITE RESULT-REC
    CLOSE RESULT-FILE
    
    GOBACK.
END PROGRAM MainBlocksMaximumStateId_TC-1.

